  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development, by virtue of its, location, scale and design, would be an incongruous, inappropriate and out of keeping form of development which would  be detrimental to the character and prevailing pattern of development in the area. The proposal is therefore contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policy D4 of the London Plan 2021, Policy CP30 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010) and Policies DMD7, DMD8, and DMD37 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014).\r",
    "The proposed development, by virtue of its lack of access for vehicles and pedestrians, including access for emergency vehicles and for vehicles managing waste, would result in substandard accommodation future occupiers.  The proposal is therefore contrary to Policies D4, D5, D6, and D12  of the London Plan (2021), Core Policies 4, 25 and 30 of the Core Strategy (2010) and Policies DMD8, DMD9, DMD 45 DMD 47 and DMD 48  of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014) and  the Enfield Waste and Recycling Storage Planning Guidance (2020).",
    "The proposed development, by virtue of its insufficient separation distance from no. 1a Sedcote Road, would have a detrimental impact on the residential amenities of existing occupiers of number 1a and future occupiers of the new dwelling through loss of light, inadequate privacy, loss of outlook, overshowing and creating a heightened sense of enclosure. The proposal is therefore contrary to Core Policy 30 of the Council's Core Strategy (2010) and Policies DMD8, DMD 14 and DMD 37 of the Council's Development Management Document (2014).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of an adequate  sustainable drainage strategy, fails to demonstrate how the proposal will  manage the risk of flooding and utilise Sustainable Urban Drainage Systems (SuDS) following the drainage hierarchy in the London Plan. The proosal is therefore contrary to Section 14 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policies SI 12 and SI 13 of the London Plan (2021), CP28 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010) and DMD61 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014)."
  ],
